"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-11-canadas-b-boy-phil-wizard-wins-first-olympic-breaking-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - Canada's B-Boy Phil Wizard won the inaugural Olympic Men's Breaking gold in Paris on Saturday and said he hopes it \\\"opens doors to people\\\" involved in the high-energy dance sport.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9937439983687825, \"rank\": 0.004322995336977263, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 22, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6215964570003871, \"rank\": 0.43122490344979586, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998228759, \"rank\": 1.7718408731480898e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard, whose real name is Philip Kim, beat France's B-Boy Dany Dann in the final amid the opulent grandeur of Place de la Concorde, with B-Boy Victor of the US taking bronze.\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 235, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"score\": 0.9999999991202912, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9937439983687825, \"rank\": 0.004322995336977263, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 319, \"end\": 339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 0.9999999939686859, \"rank\": 6.031398676744772e-09, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.003215140582273e-33, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}, {\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9998918247225869, \"rank\": 7.110544160246994e-05, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"score\": 0.6608407767260822, \"rank\": 0.32692681045006944, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_Hot_100\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking, better known as breakdancing, is making its first and possibly last appearance at the Olympics, having been left off the programme for Los Angeles 2028.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard said breaking was \\\"an underappreciated sport\\\" and hoped its Olympic debut would change people's minds.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope that today was a perfect example of showing the world how incredible breaking is - that was truly my only goal here,\\\" said the 27-year-old, a former world champion.\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so grateful and so happy to come out with the win, but more than anything I just wanted to show the world what breaking is.\\\"\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition saw 16 dancers, known as B-Boys, going head-to-head in a series of battles, starting with a pool stage before moving to a knockout round.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Wizard had the crowd against him in the final against local hero Dany Dann, a 36-year-old with blue hair whose real name is Danis Civil.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Canadian soon had them eating out of his hand thanks to his incredible routine, for which the judges awarded him a 3-0 victory.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9187578851408269, \"rank\": 0.08834582521393003, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was stressed out of my mind,\\\" said Phil Wizard.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's been a whirlwind of emotion.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cried my eyes out because I was so scared to do this.\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been a lot of pressure, a lot of expectations - I am glad I was able to deliver.\\\"\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The B-Boys perform on a circular stage, accompanied by DJs pumping out hip hop classics and MCs hyping up the crowd.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking originated in the block parties held in the Bronx in New York in the 1970s.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 0.9999999997526174, \"rank\": 2.4743182659939363e-10, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 1823, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999996592698501, \"rank\": 3.3931926476082943e-06, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan's B-Girl Ami won the women's gold on Friday, beating Lithuania's B-Girl Nicka in the final.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.6904746038562627, \"rank\": 0.24086767038583398, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9998653137442298, \"rank\": 0.00010918879276608859, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": []}]}"